## Publishing on GitHub Pages

To publish this guide on GitHub Pages, we've prepared a detailed step-by-step instruction in the [GITHUB_PAGES_GUIDE.md](GITHUB_PAGES_GUIDE.md) file.

Brief overview of the process:

1. Create a new repository on GitHub
2. Set up authentication (Personal Access Token or SSH keys)
3. Push your code to GitHub:
   ```bash
   git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/llama4-maverick-finetuning.git
   git branch -M main
   git push -u origin main
   ```
4. Enable GitHub Pages in the repository settings (Settings -> Pages -> Source -> GitHub Actions)
5. Wait for the publication process to complete

After that, your site will be available at: `https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/llama4-maverick-finetuning/`

